You are implementing the SSE log panel React component (`components/SseLogPanel.tsx`) for a video production pipeline editor. This client component streams real-time job output from EventSource, displays a scrollable auto-tailing log, and shows completion/error banners.

Requirements
1. Props: `jobId: string | null`, `onDone?: () => void`, `onError?: (msg: string) => void`, `className?: string`.
2. When `jobId` is null, render nothing (return null).
3. When `jobId` is set, open an `EventSource` at `/api/jobs/${jobId}/stream`.
4. Append incoming `data` events as `[HH:MM:SS] message` lines to a log buffer (state array).
5. On `event: done`, show a green success banner `âś“ Completed` and call `onDone()`.
6. On `event: error`, show a red error banner `âś• Error: {message}` and call `onError(message)`.
7. Auto-scroll to bottom on each new log line (use `useEffect` with scroll ref).
8. Fall back to polling `GET /api/jobs/${jobId}` every 2s if EventSource fails or is not supported.
9. Virtualize the log list using CSS `contain: strict; overflow-y: auto` for large log volumes (no external lib required).
10. Close EventSource on component unmount or when `jobId` changes.
11. `'use client'` directive at the top.

