Instructions
- Use `useRef<EventSource | null>(null)` to hold the EventSource instance.
- `useEffect` dependencies: `[jobId]`. On cleanup: `eventSource.current?.close()`.
- Timestamp format: `new Date().toLocaleTimeString('en-US', { hour12: false })` â†’ `HH:MM:SS`.
- Log container: `<div ref={logRef} className="overflow-y-auto max-h-64 font-mono text-xs bg-black/20 p-2 rounded">`.
- Auto-scroll: `logRef.current?.scrollTo({ top: logRef.current.scrollHeight, behavior: 'smooth' })`.
- Success banner: `<div className="mt-2 text-green-400 font-mono text-sm">âś“ Completed</div>`.
- Error banner: `<div className="mt-2 text-red-400 font-mono text-sm">âś• Error: {errorMsg}</div>`.
- Polling fallback: `const interval = setInterval(() => fetch(...), 2000)` started only when EventSource constructor throws.
- Parse event data: `const data = JSON.parse(event.data)` for `message` field extraction.

Deliverable
